ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I have a good understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the fixe
s:\n\n**Blocking Issue 1: ProviderNotFoundException for ImBloc**\n- Change `regi
sterFactory<ImBloc>` to `registerLazySingleton<ImBloc>` in di.dart\n- In `app.da
rt`, wrap `MaterialApp.router` with `BlocProvider(create: (_) => getIt<ImBloc>()
)`\n- Remove local `BlocProvider` in `/chat` route\n- In `ChatPage.dispose()`, r
emove `ImDisconnectRequested`, instead send `ImSetCurrentConversation(conversati
onId: null)`\n\n**Major Issue 2: Socket lifecycle**\n- Same fix as blocking issu
e - global singleton, connect/disconnect managed at app level not page level\n- 
In `ChatPage.initState()`, remove `ImConnectRequested` (moved to app level)\n- I
n `ChatPage.dispose()`, remove disconnect, just set current conversation to null
\n\n**Major Issue 3: Cross-conversation message buffering**\n- Add `Map<String, 
List<MessageItem>> _messageBuffer` in `ImBloc`\n- In `_onMessageReceived`, if me
ssage is for different conversation, buffer it\n- In `_onSetCurrentConversation`
, when switching, merge buffered messages for that conversation into `_messages`
and clear buffer\n\n**Major Issue 4: delivered status never set**\n- Add `Messag
eDeliveredEvent` to shared-types\n- Update `im-events.yaml` with `message:delive
red` event\n- Update `ImGateway.handleSendMessage` to emit `message:delivered` t
o sender after `message:receive` to receiver\n- Update `ImSocketClient` to handl
e `message:delivered`\n- Update `ImBloc` to handle delivered event and update st
atus from `sent` to `delivered`\n\n**Major Issue 5: @MaxLength on image messages
**\n- Fix `SendMessageDto.content` validation with `@ValidateIf((o) => o.type ==
= "text")`\n\n**Major Issue 6: Add Flutter unit tests**\n- Add `im_bloc_test.dar
t`\n- Add `conversation_list_cubit_test.dart`\n\n**Minor Issue 7: pagination cur
sor with updated_at**\n- Fix `getConversations` to use composite cursor `(update
d_at, conversation_id)`\n\n**Minor Issue 8: last_message required**\n- Remove `l
ast_message` from required in `im.yaml`\n- Check if generated models need update
\n\n**Minor Issue 9: Maestro optional assertions**\n- Fix `send_message.yaml` an
d `view_conversation_list.yaml`\n\n**Minor Issue 10: PushService tech debt**\n- 
Add entry to `tech-debt-tracker.md`\n\nLet me start implementing these fixes. I 
need to be careful about the order - some files depend on others.\n\nLet me also
check how the app connects the ImBloc globally. Since the review says to connect
at app level on auth, I need to add that logic. The best place is in `app.dart` 
- in the `BlocListener<AuthBloc, AuthState>` we can connect/disconnect the ImBlo
c.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the review recommendation:\n1. `regist
erLazySingleton` for ImBloc\n2. Wrap `MaterialApp.router` with `BlocProvider(cre
ate: (_) => getIt<ImBloc>())`\n3. Remove local BlocProvider in ChatPage route\n4
. In ChatPage.dispose(), don\'t call ImDisconnectRequested, instead reset curren
t conversation\n\nFor the global connection, I should connect the ImBloc when au
th becomes authenticated, and disconnect when unauthenticated. Let me add that t
o `_SocialWorldAppBodyState.build()` via a `BlocListener`.\n\nWait, the review s
ays "Socket 在登录后保持长连接，仅在注销或 App 后台时断开". The simplest approac
h within the current architecture is to add a BlocListener for AuthBloc that con
nects/disconnects ImBloc.\n\nActually, looking at app.dart again - there\'s alre
ady a `BlocListener<AuthBloc, AuthState>` in `_SocialWorldAppBodyState.build()`.
I can extend that listener to manage the ImBloc connection.\n\nBut there\'s a co
mplication - `AuthBloc` is provided at the `SocialWorldApp` level, and `ImBloc` 
would also be at that level (wrapped around MaterialApp.router). So inside the B
locListener, we can do `context.read<ImBloc>()`.\n\nLet me now implement all fix
es.\n\nFirst, let me update the todo list.',
